messageBody:
Paul Vandenbrink scripsit:

> Maybe you mean the Calm/On distinction.

What we call LOT vs. PALM around here.

> That is something specific to a British Pronunciation.
> Americans say Ah (calm) instead of On.

Well, except Eastern New Englanders. Canadians don't do
this either, nor do anglophones from the Caribbean and
the Southern Hemisphere.

--
John Cowan cowan@... http://ccil.org/~cowan

that optimum or inadequate performance in the trend of competitive
activities exhibits no tendency to be commensurate with innate capacity,
but that a considerable element of the unpredictable must invariably be
taken into account. --Ecclesiastes 9:11, Orwell/Brown version
